    • Method Detail

      • validateDynamicFrameConnection

        public static ISunriseSensorModuleConnection validateDynamicFrameConnection(com.kuka.geometry.connections.IFrameConnection dynamicFrameConnection)
        Checks whether a dynamic frame connection is an active transformation provider of type ISunriseSensorModuleConnection, so that it can be used in a Frame Graph mapping in Sunrise RT.
        If an active transformation provider of correct type is available, it will be returned, otherwise an exception is thrown.
        Parameters:
        dynamicFrameConnection - the dynamic frame connection that should be validated
        Returns:
        ISunriseSensorModuleConnection
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the transformation provider is of wrong type
        IllegalStateException - if the transformation provider is not active
        This element is an undocumented internal feature. It is not intended to be used by applications as it might change or be removed in future versions.

      • staticTargetFrameMapping

        public static FrameDefinitionList staticTargetFrameMapping(FrameDefinitionList frameGraph,
                                                           com.kuka.math.geometry.Transformation flange2Tool,
                                                           com.kuka.geometry.FrameChain targetToRoot)
        Configures the frame graph so that the transformation from robot root to robot flange for a given target frame can be computed.
        This function handles only static task frames that are not connected to the robot flange. The resulting frame graph will look like this:

        FF - AF
        |
        RF
        |
        WF - TF - CA

        CA corresponds to the target frame. Note that an implicit loop closure is performed by the Sunrise Core between CA and AF, so that the transformation from RF to FF can be computed for each time step.
        Parameters:
        frameGraph - the frame definitions
        flange2Tool - the transformation from flange to tool
        targetToRoot - the frame chain from target to root
        Returns:
        the configured frameDefinitionList
        This element is an undocumented internal feature. It is not intended to be used by applications as it might change or be removed in future versions.

      • taskFrameMapping

        public static void taskFrameMapping(FrameDefinitionList frameGraph,
                                    SunriseMappingToken info,
                                    com.kuka.geometry.SpatialObject robot,
                                    DeviceMappingResult robotPorts,
                                    com.kuka.geometry.FrameChain targetToRoot,
                                    com.kuka.geometry.FrameChainElement taskFrame)
        Configures the frame to be used for interpolation on a (possibly dynamic) task frame.
        Three subgraphs will be created. One for computing the task frame relative Cartesian commanded position. One for computing the task frame relative Cartesian measured position. And one for computing the absolute task frame position.
        This function handles both static and dynamic task frames, as long as the target frame is not connected to the robot flange. The resulting frame graph will look like this:

        FF_Msr - AF_Msr
        |
        | FF_CmdT1m - AF_CmdT1m
        | /
        RF
        |
        WF - (AuxFrame) - TF
        `(AuxFrame) - TF_Msr

        TODO: split this function into three functions, one for each use case.
        Parameters:
        frameGraph - the frame definitions
        info - the sunrise mapping token
        robot - the robot
        robotPorts - the robot ports
        targetToRoot - the frame chain from target frame to root frame
        taskFrame - the frame chain element corresponding to the (possibly dynamic) task frame (reference CS for interpolation)
        This element is an undocumented internal feature. It is not intended to be used by applications as it might change or be removed in future versions.

      • searchTaskFrame

        public static com.kuka.geometry.FrameChainElement searchTaskFrame(com.kuka.geometry.FrameChain targetToRoot,
                                                                  com.kuka.geometry.SpatialObject robot,
                                                                  boolean allowTaskFrameOnFlange,
                                                                  boolean allowOnlyOneDynamicFrameOnPath)
        Search the (possibly dynamic) task frame for the motion interpolation in the configured scenegraph.

        It is also checked whether the task frame is connected to a robots flange and an exception is thrown if this is not allowed.

        Parameters:
        targetToRoot - the frame chain from the target frame to its root frame
        robot - the robot used for task frame checks
        allowTaskFrameOnFlange - true if the task frame is allowed to be connected to the robots flange
        allowOnlyOneDynamicFrameOnPath - true if an exception should be thrown when more than one dynamic frame is on the path from the target frame to the root frame
        Returns:
        the task frame (either world or the first parent with a dynamic transformation on the path to world)
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the task frame is below the robot flange and this is not allowed
        IllegalArgumentException - if more than one dynamic frame is on the path to root and this is not allowed
        IllegalArgumentException - if the target frame is not connected to the robot
        This element is an undocumented internal feature. It is not intended to be used by applications as it might change or be removed in future versions.
